					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">When you program in C with CC65, it needs some variables to do certain stuff: ptr1, ptr2, ptr3, sp and maybe some other things.<br /><br />My question: How are these variables stored in memory and do I have to adjust my config file accordingly, so that my variables don't overlap with them?<br /><br />To elaborate:<br /><br />Are these variables stored in absolute memory locations in the zero page, so that I have to declare my zero page segment as going from address $0008 and being 248 bytes long instead of starting at $0000 and being 256 bytes long?<br /><br />Or do these variables internally use the segment names as well, like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">.segment &quot;ZEROPAGE&quot;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; prt1: .res 2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; prt2: .res 2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; prt3: .res 2<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; sp: .res 2</div>so that they can never overlap with my own variables if I use the segment declaration?</div>

					
