				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you don't declare the segment properly as zeropage in the assembly source, it means that all your instructions that access ZP variables will contain an extra byte, and take extra cycles, because the assembler will be using the absolute address form instead. It's really worth typing those extra 10 characters in.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
